<subSubSection pageId="2" pageNumber="153" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="2.[113,765,1726,1942]" lastBlockId="2.[838,1490,1376,1624]" pageId="2" pageNumber="153">
<emphasis box="[151,257,1726,1750]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="153">History. –</emphasis>
In the protologue 
<bibRefCitation author="VISIANI, R. DE" box="[456,614,1726,1750]" firstAuthor="VISIANI" journalOrPublisher="Amico Campi" pageId="2" pageNumber="153" pagination="113 - 115" part="1" refId="ref2560" refString="VISIANI, R. DE (1865). Di un nuovo giglio nella Dalmazia. Amico Campi 1: 113 - 115." title="Di un nuovo giglio nella Dalmazia" type="journal article" year="1865">VISIANI (1865)</bibRefCitation>
distinguished this variety from typical 
<taxonomicName box="[377,539,1758,1782]" class="Liliopsida" family="Liliaceae" genus="Lilium" kingdom="Plantae" order="Liliales" pageId="2" pageNumber="153" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="martagon">
<emphasis box="[377,502,1758,1782]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="153">L.martagon</emphasis>
L.
</taxonomicName>
in having “ 
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="153">L. phyllis perianthii extus glaberrimis, intus rubro-venosis unicoloribus”</emphasis>
. In PAD we traced a specimen (individual on the left side) having the original Visiani’s autograph description of this taxon which is identical to the description given in the protologue. Moreover, Visiani refers to Maria de Cattani as the collector and Much (Muć) locality (Croatia) as the collection site, both of which are mentioned on the herbarium label. Thus this specimen can be considered as original material collected from the “locus classicus” and is designated here as the lectotype. On the same herbarium sheet (specimen on the right side) is also a plant referable to 
<taxonomicName box="[1107,1244,1536,1560]" class="Liliopsida" family="Liliaceae" genus="Lilium" kingdom="Plantae" order="Liliales" pageId="2" pageNumber="153" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="martagon">
<emphasis box="[1107,1244,1536,1560]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="153">L. martagon</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
collected on Biokovo (Croatia): “ 
<taxonomicName authority="Martagon L." authorityName="Martagon L." box="[967,1186,1568,1592]" class="Liliopsida" family="Liliaceae" genus="Lilium" kingdom="Plantae" order="Liliales" pageId="2" pageNumber="153" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[967,1155,1568,1592]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="153">Lilium Martagon</emphasis>
L.
</taxonomicName>
/ In umbrosis sylvatices mt Biokovo / Visiani s.d., s.n.”.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="2.[839,1490,1640,1888]" pageId="2" pageNumber="153">
<emphasis box="[877,1135,1640,1664]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="153">Taxonomic discussion. –</emphasis>
The selected lectotype fully confirms the close relationship between 
<taxonomicName box="[1215,1342,1672,1696]" class="Liliopsida" family="Liliaceae" genus="Lilium" kingdom="Plantae" order="Liliales" pageId="2" pageNumber="153" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="martagon">
<emphasis box="[1215,1342,1672,1696]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="153">L. martagon</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName class="Liliopsida" family="Liliaceae" genus="Lilium" kingdom="Plantae" order="Liliales" pageId="2" pageNumber="153" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="variety" species="martagon" variety="cattaniae">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="153">L. martagon</emphasis>
var. 
<emphasis box="[932,1033,1704,1728]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="153">cattaniae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and therefore the varietal rank is the most appropriate, which is also suggested by recent molecular analysis as it failed to distinguish the two taxa at a specific level (
<bibRefCitation author="MURATOVIC, E. &amp; O. HIDALGO &amp; T. GARNATJE &amp; S. SILJAK- YAKOVLEV" box="[846,1091,1800,1824]" etAl="&amp; al." firstAuthor="MURATOVIC" journalOrPublisher="Advanced Sci. Lett." pageId="2" pageNumber="153" pagination="180 - 189" part="3" refId="ref2294" refString="MURATOVIC, E., O. HIDALGO, T. GARNATJE &amp; S. SILJAK- YAKOVLEV (2010). Molecular phylogeny and genome size in European lilies (genus Lilium, Liliaceae). Advanced Sci. Lett. 3: 180 - 189." title="Molecular phylogeny and genome size in European lilies (genus Lilium, Liliaceae)" type="journal article" year="2010">MURATOVIĆ &amp; al., 2010</bibRefCitation>
). The Linnaean taxon 
<taxonomicName box="[1317,1443,1800,1824]" class="Liliopsida" family="Liliaceae" genus="Lilium" kingdom="Plantae" order="Liliales" pageId="2" pageNumber="153" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="martagon">
<emphasis box="[1317,1443,1800,1824]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="153">L. martagon</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was also recently typified by 
<bibRefCitation author="PERUZZI, L. &amp; C. E. JARVIS" box="[1091,1348,1832,1856]" firstAuthor="PERUZZI" journalOrPublisher="Taxon" pageId="2" pageNumber="153" pagination="1359 - 1365" part="58" refId="ref2393" refString="PERUZZI, L. &amp; C. E. JARVIS (2009). Typification of Linnaean names in Liliaceae. Taxon 58: 1359 - 1365." title="Typification of Linnaean names in Liliaceae" type="journal article" year="2009">PERUZZI &amp; JARVIS (2009)</bibRefCitation>
and the specimen from LINN (sheet No. 420.5) was selected as lectotype.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
